Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan
with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring to a boil.

Add the @egg noodle nest{2} to the water and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them 
sticking together.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlicclove{2}(peeled and grated).

Cut the @tenderstem broccoli{150%g} into thirds.

Trim the @pak choi{1} and thinly slice widthways.

Slice the @sugar snap peas{80%g} in half lengthways.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the Tenderstem® broccoli and sugar snap peas. Season with
@salt and @pepper.

Stir-fry until just soft and lightly charred, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Lower the heat to medium-high, then stir in the garlic and @ginger puree{15%g}.
Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour the @gochujang paste{50%g}, @soy sauce{25%ml}, @ketjap manis{25%ml}, 
@honey{1} and @water for the sauce{100%ml} into the veg pan. Stir well to
combine, then add the pak choi.

Bring to the boil, then simmer until the sauce has thickened slightly,
~{2-3%minutes}.

In the meantime, crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet
using a #rolling pin{}.

Add the cooked noodles to the veg and toss to coat in the sauce.

Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a splash of water if it needs loosening.

Share your gochujang veggie noodles between your bowls.

Sprinkle over the peanuts to finish. Enjoy!